    p
      | This repo will be kept in sync via a Jenkins build&comma; and represents a static HTML version of the design&period;
    h2#installation Installation
    h3#dependencies Dependencies
    p
      a(href='http://nodejs.org/') NodeJS
      | v0&period;10&plus; &lpar;look into
      a(href='https://github.com/creationix/nvm')
        code nvm
      | for keeping up to date&rpar;
    ul
      li
        | Command line utilities&colon;
        code grunt
      li
        | NPM packages&colon;
        code package&period;json
      li
        | Optional dependencies&colon;
        code node-canvas
    h4#installing-grunt Installing Grunt
    p
      | In a local terminal&comma;
      code npm install -g grunt-cli
      | &period; This will install the grunt command line interface globally&period;
    h4#installing-npm-packages Installing NPM packages
    p
      | In project directory&comma; run
      code npm install
      | &period; This will install the tasks and helpers for Grunt &amp; the project&comma; including&colon;
    ul
      li
        a(href='http://jade-lang.com') Jade
        | - HTML templating
      li
        a(href='http://learnboost.github.io/stylus/') Stylus
        | - Logical CSS preprocessor
      li &mldr;and other helpful web technologies&period;
    h4#installing-optional-dependencies Installing optional dependencies
    p
      a(href='https://github.com/learnboost/node-canvas')
        code node-canvas
      | is used by
      a(href='http://visionmedia.github.io/nib/') Nib
      | to generate base64 encoded PNGs for use as background images&comma; e&period;g&period; gradients&period; Falls back to CSS3 gradients if not available on development environment&period;
    h5#mac-osx-installation Mac OSX installation
    ul
      li
        | Install
        a(href='https://xquartz.macosforge.org/landing/') XQuartz
        | &period;
      li
        | Run
        code brew update &amp;&amp; brew doctor
        | to check if your system is up to date&period; &lpar;requires
        a(href='http://brew.sh/') Homebrew
        | &rpar;
      li
        | Install image processing utils with
        code brew install giflib libpng jpeg
      li
        | Install
        a(href='http://cairographics.org/') Cairo
        | with
        code brew install cairo
      li
        | Finally&comma; install
        code node-canvas
        | with
        code npm install canvas
        | &period; You may need to
        code export PKG&UnderBar;CONFIG&UnderBar;PATH
        | as discussed in the
        a(href='https://github.com/LearnBoost/node-canvas/wiki/Installation---OSX') wiki
        | after the Cairo step&period;
    p
      | The above maze is why
      code node-canvas
      | is an optional dependency&period; Once installed&comma; it drastically slows down Stylus compilation time&comma; but can embed a generated image in CSS as a
      code data-uri
      | &period;
    h2#developing Developing
    p
      | Once everything is installed&comma; run
      code grunt
      | in the project directory&period; This runs the
      code default
      | Grunt task&period; It will compile the source code into a working static site&comma; launch a
      a(href='http://www.senchalabs.org/connect/') connect
      | HTTP server&comma; open your browser to the launched server&comma; and watch files for changes&period;
    h3#source-code-compilation Source Code Compilation
    p
      | The main purpose of the front-end build system&period; Split into
      code markup
      | &comma;
      code scripts
      | &comma; and
      code styles
      | &comma; these main tasks take the Jade&comma; Stylus&comma; and Javascript source and package it up for the Web&period; By default&comma; builds HTML including concatenated &amp; minified Javacript and CSS&period; With a
      code grunt --dev
      | option supplied&comma; it will use unminified source files for debugging&period;
    p Optionally run with&colon;
    ul
      li
        code grunt markup
      li
        code grunt scripts
      li
        code grunt styles
      li
        code grunt main
        | - Compiles markup&comma; scripts&comma; and styles in series&period;
      li
        code grunt concurrent&colon;main
        | - Compiles markup&comma; scripts&comma; and styles in parallel&period;
    h3#http-server HTTP Server
    p
      | By default&comma; launches on port 8000&period; Will read
      code &dollar;PORT
      | environment variable&period; Opens browser once launched&period; Includes LiveReload client script on served HTML&period;
    p Optionally run with&colon;
    ul
      li
        code grunt server
        | - Handy alias&period;
      li
        code grunt connect&colon;site&colon;keepalive
        | - Original task form&period;
      li
        code grunt concurrent&colon;server
        | - Concurrently run server &amp; watchers&period;
    h3#watchers Watchers
    p
      | The following 5 watchers are included in the
      code default
      | task &lpar;via
      code concurrent&colon;server
      | &rpar;&colon;
    ul
      li
        | If a source file changes&comma; Grunt will recompile the necessary files &lpar;
        code scripts
        | &comma;
        code styles
        | or
        code markup
        | &rpar;&period;
      li
        | If a public asset changes while watching and browsing on the
        code connect
        | webserver&comma;
        a(href='http://livereload.com/')
          code LiveReload
        | will kick in &lpar;powered by Grunt&semi; no additional software necessary&rpar;&period;
      li
        | If a Javascript file changes &lpar;Grunt config or Web script&rpar;&comma; Grunt will run
        code jshint
        | on the changed file&period;
    p
      | For a full list of available tasks&comma; run
      code grunt --help
      | &period;
